llowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/324891.html?thread=17760539#t17760539","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/324891.html?thread=17760539#t17760539","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/324891.html?thread=17760539#t17760539","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"ext_1880800","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://www.facebook.com/fantamic","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":17760539,"talkid":69377,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/324891.html?thread=17760539#t17760539","upictitle":"Colin: pic#121022210","article":"I also eagerly devoured his novels as a teenager and now feel inspired to re-read them. I loved his fast-paced stories and brilliantly preposterous dialogue. Let's hope that some of his more obscure - but still very worthwhile - work will now be re-publishedâ€¦","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"3 years ago","ctime":"May 30 2013, 09:29:45 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://www.facebook.com/fantamic","striked":null,"journaltype":"I","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/icons/facebook-16.png?v=29916?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"Colin Shaw","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":1,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"ext_1880800","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://www.livejournal.com/profile?userid=64511758&t=I","alias":0}],"dname":"Colin Shaw","ctime_ts":1369906185,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/103841605/10865290","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/324891.html?thread=17760795#t17760795","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/324891.html?thread=17760795#t17760795","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/324891.html?thread=17760795#t17760795","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"philmophlegm","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://philmophlegm.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":17760795,"talkid":69378,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/324891.html?thread=17760795#t17760795","upictitle":"philmophlegm: Dying Earth","article":"It's extremely difficult to write a tribute to Vance because compared to his prose, anything I write would appear clumsy and awkward. <br /><br />Instead, I will reproduce one of my favourite pieces of writing in all of SF and Fantasy. It's the opening paragraph of 'Emphyrio'. Vance was able to create images like this remarkably frequently.<br /><br />\"In the chamber at the top of the tower were six individuals: three who chose to call themselves \"lords\" or sometimes \"remedials\"; a wretched underling who was their prisoner; and two Garrion. The chamber was dramatic and queer: of irregular dimension, hung with panels of heavy maroon velvet. At one end an embrasure admitted a bar of light: this of a smoky amber quality, as if the pane were clogged with dust - which it was not; in fact the glass was a subtle sort, producing remarkable effects. At the opposite end of the room was a low trapezoidal door of black skeel.\"","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"3 years ago","ctime":"May 30 2013, 10:32:25 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://philmophlegm.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"philmophlegm","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"philmophlegm","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://philmophlegm.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"philmophlegm","ctime_ts":1369909945,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/120336674/61365104","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/324891.html?thread=17761051#t17761051","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/324891.html?thread=17761051#t17761051","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/324891.html?thread=17761051#t17761051","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"valle2134","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://valle2134.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":17761051,"talkid":69379,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/324891.html?thread=17761051#t17761051","upictitle":"valle2134: pic#120336674","article":"A very sad day indeed. One of our greatest writers in any genre has passed. My first Jack Vance experience was reading THE DEMON PRINCES which blew me away. Since then, whenever a Vance book came out, I had to get it and loose myself in his marvelous creations.THE DYING EARTH is his most enduring creation.I am lucky to have a copy of that book signed by Vance  And the language! Jack was a first-rate wordsmith. Sometimes you may have had to look up one of his words in a dictionary, or google it as we say nowadays, but it was worth it. Reading Vance educated and changed you. His kind will sorely be missed. Read Vance, the experience will change you.","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"3 years ago","ctime":"May 30 2013, 10:57:42 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"Jack Vance&#39;s Legacy","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://valle2134.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"valle2134","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"valle2134","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://valle2134.livejour